label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pN1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with micrometastasis in regional lymph node(s).  Micrometastases are diagnosed after sentinel or elective lymphadenectomy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Refractory Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma that is resistant to treatment.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pN1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with macrometastasis in regional lymph node(s).  Macrometastases are defined as clinically detectable nodal metastases confirmed by therapeutic lymphadenectomy or needle biopsy. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with in transit metastasis.  In transit metastasis is defined as a tumor distinct from the primary lesion and located either (1) between the primary lesion and the draining regional lymph nodes or (2) distal to the primary lesion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis beyond regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to skin, subcutaneous tissues or distant lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to lung. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma pM1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to all other visceral sites. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Nephrogenic Rest

value.value: Remnants of nephrogenic blastema cells in the kidney following embryonic development.

label.value: Perilobar Nephrogenic Rest

value.value: A nephrogenic rest found at the periphery of the renal lobe.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system. TNM clinical findings are based on clinical inspection and palpation of the involved area and the regional lymph nodes and/or radiologic studies.  The TNM clinical and pathologic primary tumor classifications of Merkel cell carcinoma are the same. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE).

label.value: Intralobar Nephrogenic Rest

value.value: A nephrogenic rest found within the renal lobe.

label.value: Hemihypertrophy

value.value: A finding indicating the presence of greater than normal asymmetry between the right and left sides of the body. The asymmetry may be manifested in the entire side or part of it.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  The TNM clinical and pathologic regional lymph nodes classifications of Merkel cell carcinoma are not the same. TNM clinical regional lymph nodes findings are based on clinical inspection and palpation of the regional lymph nodes and/or radiologic studies. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with negative regional lymph nodes by clinical examination (inspection, palpation, and/or imaging).  No pathologic node examination is performed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis in regional lymph node(s). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma in transit metastasis.  In transit metastasis is defined as a tumor distinct from the primary lesion and located either (1) between the primary lesion and the draining regional lymph nodes or (2) distal to the primary lesion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of Merkel cell carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma without distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ligand-Independent Chloride Ion Channel Activation

value.value: A process that involves the detection of and alteration of either the voltage or pH across a membrane, and results in a chloride channel becoming permeable to Cl- and related ions, including HCO3-, I-, SCN- and NO3-. This interaction plays a crucial role in setting the potential of the resting membrane, but also functions to regulate pH, the transport of organic solutes and the migration, differentiation and proliferation of cells.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage II Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).

label.value: Voltage-Gated Potassium Ion Channel Activation

value.value: A process that involves detection of alteration to the voltage across a membrane, and results in opening of the channel to become selectively permeable to potassium ions. This interaction plays a crucial role in setting the potential of the resting membrane.

label.value: Voltage-Gated Sodium Ion Channel Activation

value.value: A process that involves detection of alteration to the voltage across a membrane, and results in opening of the channel to become selectively permeable to sodium ions. This interaction plays a key role in conduction of nerve impulses throughout the central and peripheral nervous systems. Deficiencies in this process may result in various channelopathies, featuring epilepsy, seizures and paralysis.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis beyond regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to skin, subcutaneous tissues or distant lymph nodes.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to lung. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma cM1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Merkel cell carcinoma with metastasis to all other visceral sites. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ophthalmic Sites Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of ophthalmic sites cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The surgical nature of the histopathology specimen should be noted including incisional biopsy, excisional biopsy, wide local excision, radical excision including exenteration.  The specimen should be carefully oriented and inked for margin evaluation.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with tumor measuring 5 mm or less in greatest dimension and not invading the tarsal plate or eyelid margin. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with tumor measuring more than 5 mm, but not more than 10 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, any tumor invading the tarsal plate or eyelid margin.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with tumor measuring more than 10 mm, but not more than 20 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, tumor involving the full thickness of eyelid.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT3a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with tumor measuring more than 20 mm in greatest dimension.  Or, any tumor invading adjacent ocular or orbital structures.  Or, any T with perineural tumor invasion.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT3b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid for which complete tumor resection requires enucleation, exenteration, or bone resection.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Unresectable carcinoma of the eyelid due to extensive invasion of ocular, orbital, and craniofacial structures, or brain. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage IV Diffuse Large B-Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or isolated extralymphatic organ involvement in the absence of adjacent regional lymph node involvement, but in conjunction with disease in distant site(s); or any involvement of the liver or bone marrow, lungs (other than by direct extension from another site), or cerebrospinal fluid.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with no regional lymph node metastasis, based upon lymph node biopsy. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for carcinoma of the eyelid. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
